The paper discusses deep generative models and their latent spaces, which are commonly studied in the machine learning subfield of generative modeling (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of heuristic measures to find meaningful distances in latent space, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper further discusses the use of transformations to smooth out latent spaces, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the structure of learned data distributions, which is a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
